article.headline: Florida A&M 85, Howard 75
article.story: strdfjk TALLAHASSEE, Fla. (AP) -- Darius Glover came off the bench to lead five Rattlers in double digits with 22 points as Florida A&M pulled away from Howard for a 85-75 conference win Monday night. Florida A&M (16-12, 10-5 MEAC) shot 60-percent from the field, out-rebounded the Bison 32-21, and outscored them 40-16 in the paint. Brian Greene had a double-double with 16 points and 11 rebounds. Greene scored all 16 points in the second half for the Rattlers, who also got 12 points from Rome Sanders. Lamar Twitty scored 11, and Leslie Robison added 10. Howard (9-17, 5-9 MEAC) made 17 3-pointers in the game and was led by Darryl Hudson's 18 points. Will Gant added 15 for the Bison. The game was tied 39-39 at halftime, but Howard made its first three 3-point attempts of the second half and took a five-point lead. Florida A&M responded with a 14-0 run to take the control of the game, and led the rest of the way.
